# Project
Formula 1 historical analysis + race prediction. Portfolio-quality.
Built as a structured learning project: prefer clarity and explain non-obvious choices.

# Stack
- Backend: Python 3.13, FastAPI, SQLAlchemy 2.0 (typed, `Mapped[]`), Alembic, pydantic-settings.
  Install: `pip install -e ".[dev]"`. Lint: ruff. Test: pytest.
- Frontend: React + TypeScript (Vite), React Query, Recharts, Tailwind.
- DB: PostgreSQL (local via Docker; Neon in prod).
  Data sources: Jolpica/Ergast (historical, 1950+), OpenF1 (telemetry, 2023+).
- Hosting: Cloudflare Pages (FE) + Render (BE) + Neon (DB).
  Config via env vars (12-factor); never hardcode URLs or secrets.

# Engineering standards
- Surgical, minimal changes; don't refactor beyond the immediate scope.
- One correct path per feature; no speculative abstractions, no silent fallbacks.
- Fail fast: raise explicit errors when preconditions aren't met.
- Single responsibility per function; strict separation of concerns.
- TypeScript strict, no `any`. Python: full type hints; let types do the work.
- Code must build/lint/test clean before commit (`make check`).

# Layout
backend/ (app/), frontend/, infra/ (Terraform), .github/ (CI)